        Level-2 Opponent's Attack: {"claim": "The assertion that smart technology makes us dumb rests on a flawed and narrow understanding of knowledge formation and technology's role.", "argument": ["The argument that smart technology makes us dumb is based on a misunderstanding of knowledge formation.", "The argument is based on a misunderstanding of technology's role."]}
    Level-1 Your Main Claim: {"claim": "Heavy technology use impairs cognitive abilities, especially the ability to distinguish important information from trivia.", "argument": ["Stanford studies show heavy technology users perform worse on cognitive tests.", "Cognitive tests measure the ability to distinguish important information from trivia.", "Constant notifications prioritize novelty over importance.", "This diminishes the ability to focus."]}
        Level-2 Opponent's Attack: {"claim": "The assertion that smart technology makes us dumb rests on a flawed and narrow understanding of knowledge formation and technology's role.", "argument": ["The argument that smart technology makes us dumb is based on a misunderstanding of knowledge formation.", "The argument is based on a misunderstanding of technology's role."]}
